edu.bu.segrelab.comets
Class Cell

java.lang.Object
  edu.bu.segrelab.comets.Cell
All Implemented Interfaces:
CometsConstants
public abstract class Cell
extends java.lang.Object
implements CometsConstants

The basic, abstract Cell class for use with the COMETS program. As this is an abstract class, actual Cells for use in COMETS shouldn't instantiate this class directly, but only an extension class that is part of a loaded package (e.g. FBACell).

Author:
Bill Riehl
See Also:
edu.bu.segrelab.comets.fba.FBACell

run

public abstract int run()
Tells the Cell to run an internal process and return some value. This process can range from an FBA calculation, changing state based on the state of neighboring Cells, etc.

Returns:
an integer value after it is finished

eat

public abstract boolean eat()
Tells the Cell to eat from the environment.

Returns:

public abstract void move()
Tells the Cell to move, according to its internal logic.

die

public abstract int die()
Tells the Cell to die, using internally coordinated processes, (e.g., giving up excess energy to the environment)

Returns:
a value corresponding to the Cell's final state at death.

maintenance

public abstract void maintenance()
Tells the Cell to enact some form of maintenance function - consuming some energy, for example.

reproduce

public abstract Cell reproduce()
Tells the Cell to reproduce, returning a new daughter Cell.

Returns:
the new daughter Cell, or null if reproduction doesn't occur.

Returns:
the color of the Cell, packed into a single integer.

attributesString

public abstract java.lang.String attributesString()
Generates a String containing the attributes of the Cell. These may include its growth rate, movement rate, reproduction rate, etc.

Returns:
an attributes String.

statisticsString

public abstract java.lang.String statisticsString()
Generates a String containing the current statistics of the Cell. These may include its position in the world, amount of energy and food it has, etc.

Returns:
a statistics String.

getBiomass

public abstract double[] getBiomass()
Returns the array of biomasses for each Model that may be represented by the Cell. It is expected that each Cell would have access to each Model, so a double array is returned with values corresponding to the elements of the ordered Model array owned by the Comets object.

Returns:
a double array of biomass values.

changeBiomass

public abstract int changeBiomass(double[] delta)
Modify the biomass of the Cell by an array of delta values, where each element i corresponds to the ith Model currently loaded.

Parameters:
delta - - an array of values to modify each biomass component by.
Returns:
an integer implying the success or failure of the operation

backup

public abstract Cell backup(World2D backupWorld)
Returns a backup of this Cell, corresponding to the World2D being backed up in parallel.

The usage here is to create a new Cell that exists in the backupWorld parameter, and not in its current world.

Parameters:
backupWorld -
Returns:
a copy of the Cell
